BadBlanket

So I start a ship (which is still going) and selection happens not long after on C1. Everyone does what they do and end up in their respective dorms/areas. I was in the room with Eleesha, Janice, and Kuan Ti. I go play a game for a while and come back. The ship was calm, it was a new cycle. I see an interesting little shrink message and cock my eyebrow at it but decide to respond to something in the general chat passively. Suddenly Eleesha leaps out of her bed and ninja kicks poor Kuan Ti and starts beating on him before fleeing to Ian. After doing my double-take I decide to inform the crew of the brutal assault. Eleesha tried a half assed attempt to make me believe that he had transferred into her but naturally I just laughed and shrugged it off.

Chun and I began communicating and got ready to kill Eleesha. I didn't have too much ap but I did have the knife. I might as well go and do SOME damage because I wasn't sure how active the crew would be. I went in and immediately killed her in one hit with a throat slit. Mush. Coming to find out she was scared by my activity because the peculiar shrink message was a rare message that pops up when a shrink is trying to cure a mush of mental disorder.

We're now Day 6. We've managed to collect enough evidence on the second mush and have successfully stuck her with RFS. She was, indeed, mush... The second mush, you ask? None other than our Shrink Janice... Who had accidentally revealed her partner at the very beginning!

BadBlanketStory of RNG and Murphy's law joining forces against a poor mush

Since you started the story, I might as well add the worst part of the fail.

So... yeah, I was Eleesha on that ship, and I became alpha mush with Janice as a partner. Things went smoothly on the first night, I was carrying the soap and quietly extracted two spores before showering and dismantling the AD shower, then went to bed. Janice was in the same dorm, and I thought it was a little risky, but I decided it would be too suspicious to switch dorms. So I stayed in AD and went to bed, in game and in real life.

When I got up, I read the logs and was horrified to see the message I'd been dreading every time I was mush Eleesha but had never seen. Yeah, as BB said, I outed myself to my mush partner.

And of course it had to happen with two other TE members in the room (Kuan Ti and Hua). I panicked. I considered defacing the logs, which would have made all three TE people suspects, but also both alpha mush. Also, Hua was active at the time and could have seen me act. So I ruled out Defacer, warned Janice that I'd been revealed and that I was going to transfer to Chao and rampage. I tried to kill Kuan Ti, almost succeeded, and went in search of Chao. Found him in medlab, spiked him, and... and then saw that I didn't have the option to transfer, counted my skills, and realized I had already used up all four slots.

Double

Triple, actually, because I remembered that Chao was in medlab because he was waiting for Finola to cure his broken foot. The ideal transfer target indeed...

Anyway... there was I, stranded in the lab, completely outed, with no spores left, no AP, and an Ian who was completely useless because Hua managed to kill me in one hit.

Yeah, you can laugh, BB.

Grumbles again.

On may 29, 2015
fishehh

So this here fail was a big deal and blew up quite a bit in IRC..... I surprised No one posted here about it yet, but I suppose they were waiting for the AP thread or just me to post it.


I'm Gioele, the ship is another TE random jump, and all mush are dead with only 2 inactives already starved. We don't think much of going to Eden, but we figured might as well go try and get starmap fragments or whatever. Just spend our time while racking up days, you know.

Anyways, I get a few coffee's (about 4) stacked up to get ready for scanning, and manage to find this 8 zone planet right off the bat. x2 Cold temp, x2Insect, Hot temp, cristallite, swamp, forest. Needless to say we headed out right away.

Expo time comes, and seeing as I am the lucky one online at the time, I get to come along as official meat-shield with Hua, as official pilot, Chao, as our escort, and Finola, the Diplomat. Forgotten by me, and I suppose the rest of us, we had managed to lose the compass on an earlier expo for O2.

First zone, Cold. Hua lost.

Second zone, insects. Chao gets sick.

Third zone, Forest, Chao lost.

Fourth zone, wandering.

Fifth zone, Cold. Finola lost.

Sixth, hot. Crew (Me) Takes 2 damage.

Seventh, found Finola (Looking up after all)

Last (If i counted right?), Swamp. 2 damage to me and Finola.


So of course, with 2 still lost, Jin comes rushing down with Freida, meanwhile I am stipped of my title as an Astro, and banned from ever scanning in future games.

Expo #2;

First, wandered.

Second, Hua dead.

Third, Cristallite, Jin lost.

Fourth, wandered.

Fifth, Jin found.

Sixth, insects (I don't know what happened, and at that point, didn't care.)
All zones discovered.

Weren't allowed to go back and save Chao. He was hit with the MIA/all zones discovered bug.


Its not all bad though, we managed to rush the serum and return to Sol so that we could beam Chao up. I believe he brought Hua remains with him. The whole fiasco was hillarious, and as Gioele, I never broke a sweat from the expo.

Needless to say, I will won't be playing Frieda next ship. I don't think Ill ever be allowed on expos or the astro terminal again.

Edit:
TL|DR: Found great planet. 4 missing crew, 1 dead and 1 unobtainable. Banned as astro.

Blaster for non-shooter are useful just if you have Lenses. Without them you have more chance to miss shot than kick.

Blaster : Kick ratio - 25 : 24
Blaster gives small chance to headshot and big chance to injury yourself or target.

Remember: blasters are just for mature people.

On january 28, 2016
[8281990]

It's been my observation, also, that Astropad will "learn" the properties of a pill/food item per ship, and repeat that information when that item shows up again elsewhere. So if your chef/botanist updates the properties of new fruits in IB, and a player with no relevant skills updates when that fruit is moved to, say, a dorm, the properties will show up in the dorm also.

(I've also seen this when new alien fruits arrive in IB, and an unskilled person updates the properties to find that Astropad thinks they are already rotten. In reality, that fruit was eaten long ago for an emergency but the last time a skilled person checked it into Astropad, it *was* rotten.)

So... just be careful about what you do with Astropad evidence. And it's probably safer to "forget" to update in rooms with food/pills, if you're mush. Or only read and never update yourself, as if you aren't using it at all.

On january 28, 2016
PseudoDernier
Gentleman kawaiiiii

Kobb is completely right on that, when a Biologist/Chef/Botanist/etc. shares food or pills effects it is stored in another variable and applied ship-wide, and the script checks your skills in order not to reveal mushes. We'll certainly add an explanation for the next version, I've read this sort of message too many times.

But only food effects should be stored apart, not food decaying. I don't even understand how this could happen. I'll check that later, if you have any screenshots/text inventories it would be great.

Actually, that's not the case as well - the victimis picked randomly from everyone who's alive. If the targeted person has a capsule - they die, otherwise - nothing happens. But taking out a capsule means there's 1 less cycle of safety for the crew, while the person with a capsule gets a second life, basically. On february 22, 2016
Cross

Maybe I am not understanding you correctly...

If the targeted person has a capsule - they die, otherwise - nothing happens.

I believe this is the other way around. If the targeted person has a capsule they cheat death and lose the capsule, otherwise they die.

But taking out a capsule means there's 1 less cycle of safety for the crew, while the person with a capsule gets a second life, basically.

If nobody has any capsules and current oxygen is at 1 or 0, someone will die at cycle change. By taking out the last capsule when there is only one oxygen left, there is a chance (dependent on how many people are alive) that the person chosen to die will be the one holding the capsule, allowing everyone to live for another cycle. This does have the side effect of making it more likely for the person holding the capsule to survive longer than the rest because he or she needs to be selected twice to die, assuming they hold the capsule until the end.

Looks like she trusted Finola because they where pming, so just went and finished off exausted Janice. Who... was a humand ofc. Leaving us with awesome morale and no Shrink.

I allowed Finola to go back to work because we where becoming a bit low on people anyway, because we had 4 more inactive.

Meanwhile I found the seismic O2 planet just when our oxy run low, and Jin Su could have restored our morale easily when he picked up commander skill. What could go wrong? Well, seismic can go wrong... Because f*ck you, that's why.
And Chun is flying into the abyss right on the day change....
I tried to ask everyone to gather up on bridge, and listen to the speech, but Jin Su spammed it right in the IB boosting me and Raluca, and then went to bridge and said that he actually have 1 morale and no ap, and it was nice playing with us all. Great....

But Finola commited suicide the same cycle, because she haven't heard the speech at IB.

At a time I figured out at least one of inactive mushes and killed him personaly, becoming the paranoid Frieda with psychotic episodes, so i may not only try to organize everyone, but also fight my own shizoprenia, that was messing half of my chat messages.

Paola, me and Ral meanwhile are working on the Pilgred as fast as we can, and looking at the commander with his awesome morale, that is supposedly dying next turn. But on the next cycle we hear, "hey guys! I cuddled the cat so i'm okay" and that means that he forgot about that when he was going to die horribly not long ago.
